emails.body_text:
Hello Rafael , 

 

The issue is now resolved, and you should find the same origins in the dataset as on the platform 

 

Thank you for your patience and understanding 

 

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah

Customer Support

                                                                                                     saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 



 

 

DNEXT INTELLIGENCE SA | Avenue Louis-Casaï 81 | CH-1216 Cointrin

info@dnext.io <mailto:info@dnext.io>  | www.dnext.io <http://www.dnext.io/> 

 

 

From: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 
Sent: Monday, March 10, 2025 14:18
To: Rafael Bucciarelli <rafael.bucciarelli@mlp.com>; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io>
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Dear Rafael,

 

Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

 

We are currently investigating the issue and working to resolve it as quickly as possible. 

 

we will keep you updated on our progress.

 

We appreciate your patience and understanding as we work through this matter.

 

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah

Customer Support

                                                                                                     saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 



 

 

DNEXT INTELLIGENCE SA | Avenue Louis-Casaï 81 | CH-1216 Cointrin

info@dnext.io <mailto:info@dnext.io>  | www.dnext.io <http://www.dnext.io/> 

 

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> 
Sent: Thursday, March 6, 2025 15:35
To: Support Dnext <support@dnext.io>
Cc: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io>
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

Another question: I’m not seeing all the origins I see in the platform. Missing Brazil, USG among others. 

 

Thanks, 

Rafael

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Monday, January 27, 2025 2:44 PM
To: 'support@dnext.io' <support@dnext.io>
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

In addition to the question below, I have another one. 

 

How to interpret different FOB values for the same date/origin/delivery month combination?

 



 

Which to take?

 

Thanks, 
Rafael

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Monday, January 27, 2025 1:40 PM
To: support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> 
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

Is this data being updated? Latest date I see available thru the API is 2025-01-21 but on the platform I see as late as 1/24. 

 

In addition could soybeans be added to this?

 

Thanks, 

Rafael

 

From: Saber Khalfallah <jira@dnext.atlassian.net <mailto:jira@dnext.atlassian.net> > 
Sent: Wednesday, January 22, 2025 9:04 AM
To: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> >
Subject: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

—-—-—-— 

Reply above this line. 

Saber Khalfallah commented:

Hello Rafael,

Here is the code for the dataset containing data for Corn CNF to all destinations, FOB, as well as Freights:

Code: “zimb-a410fb85-d8ab-11ef-82fc-06cd53a4d901”

You will also receive automated emails notifying you each time the dataset is updated.

This will allow you to either download the file or refresh the API request.

If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah Customer Support

saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 

		

 <https://dnext.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/request/26465/attachment/15856> | DNEXT INTELLIGENCE SA : Avenue Louis-Casaï 81 : CH-1216 Cointrin info@dnext.io <mailto:info@dnext.io>  : www.dnext.io <http://www.dnext.io/>  |

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 17:05
To: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Had another question.

Would it be possible to send out an automated report when the data gets updated?

Thanks,

Rafael

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 9:00 AM
To: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Great, appreciate it!

Would be interested in corn and beans CNF to all destinations and FOB.

Don’t need flat price, just premium

Many thanks!!

Best,

Rafael

From: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 8:58 AM
To: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Hi Rafael,

Thank you for getting back to me.

Yes, we can work on making the data available via the API.

Our goal is to make the full dataset accessible so you can explore the relationships you're interested in.

We’ll get back to you with the details once it’s ready.

In the meantime, let me know if there’s anything else I can assist with.

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah Customer Support

saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 

		

 <https://dnext.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/request/26465/attachment/15856> | DNEXT INTELLIGENCE SA : Avenue Louis-Casaï 81 : CH-1216 Cointrin info@dnext.io <mailto:info@dnext.io>  : www.dnext.io <http://www.dnext.io/>  |

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 14:22
To: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Hi,

I am not sure what years/destinations I’m interested in yet, would like the entire thing to play around with relationships if possible.

Do you think it could be made available via the API?

Even if history is hard to do, would appreciate current and going forward, or even just current data and I can start a time series on my side.

Thanks,

Rafael

From: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 8:20 AM
To: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Dear Rafael,

I hope this email finds you well.

Unfortunately, the specific data you're looking for isn't directly available via our API.

This is because it results from calculations involving multiple datasets related to freights and currency conversion.

However, if you can let us know the years and destinations you’re interested in, we’d be happy to create an Excel file containing the relevant historical data for you.

Please feel free to share the specifics, and we’ll get started on compiling the information.

Looking forward to your reply.

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah Customer Support

saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io>

To: Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: historical CNF

Hi,

Are historical values for this matrix available via the API?

 <https://dnext.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/request/26465/attachment/15842> 

Best,

Rafael

emails.body_text:
Dear Rafael,

 

Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

 

We are currently investigating the issue and working to resolve it as quickly as possible. 

 

we will keep you updated on our progress.

 

We appreciate your patience and understanding as we work through this matter.

 

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah

Customer Support

                                                                                                     saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 



 

 

DNEXT INTELLIGENCE SA | Avenue Louis-Casaï 81 | CH-1216 Cointrin

info@dnext.io <mailto:info@dnext.io>  | www.dnext.io <http://www.dnext.io/> 

 

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> 
Sent: Thursday, March 6, 2025 15:35
To: Support Dnext <support@dnext.io>
Cc: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io>
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

Another question: I’m not seeing all the origins I see in the platform. Missing Brazil, USG among others. 

 

Thanks, 

Rafael

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Monday, January 27, 2025 2:44 PM
To: 'support@dnext.io' <support@dnext.io>
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

In addition to the question below, I have another one. 

 

How to interpret different FOB values for the same date/origin/delivery month combination?

 



 

Which to take?

 

Thanks, 
Rafael

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Monday, January 27, 2025 1:40 PM
To: support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> 
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

Is this data being updated? Latest date I see available thru the API is 2025-01-21 but on the platform I see as late as 1/24. 

 

In addition could soybeans be added to this?

 

Thanks, 

Rafael

 

From: Saber Khalfallah <jira@dnext.atlassian.net <mailto:jira@dnext.atlassian.net> > 
Sent: Wednesday, January 22, 2025 9:04 AM
To: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> >
Subject: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

—-—-—-— 

Reply above this line. 

Saber Khalfallah commented:

Hello Rafael,

Here is the code for the dataset containing data for Corn CNF to all destinations, FOB, as well as Freights:

Code: “zimb-a410fb85-d8ab-11ef-82fc-06cd53a4d901”

You will also receive automated emails notifying you each time the dataset is updated.

This will allow you to either download the file or refresh the API request.

If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah Customer Support

saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 

		

 <https://dnext.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/request/26465/attachment/15856> | DNEXT INTELLIGENCE SA : Avenue Louis-Casaï 81 : CH-1216 Cointrin info@dnext.io <mailto:info@dnext.io>  : www.dnext.io <http://www.dnext.io/>  |

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 17:05
To: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Had another question.

Would it be possible to send out an automated report when the data gets updated?

Thanks,

Rafael

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 9:00 AM
To: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Great, appreciate it!

Would be interested in corn and beans CNF to all destinations and FOB.

Don’t need flat price, just premium

Many thanks!!

Best,

Rafael

From: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 8:58 AM
To: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Hi Rafael,

Thank you for getting back to me.

Yes, we can work on making the data available via the API.

Our goal is to make the full dataset accessible so you can explore the relationships you're interested in.

We’ll get back to you with the details once it’s ready.

In the meantime, let me know if there’s anything else I can assist with.

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah Customer Support

saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> 

		

 <https://dnext.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/request/26465/attachment/15856> | DNEXT INTELLIGENCE SA : Avenue Louis-Casaï 81 : CH-1216 Cointrin info@dnext.io <mailto:info@dnext.io>  : www.dnext.io <http://www.dnext.io/>  |

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 14:22
To: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Hi,

I am not sure what years/destinations I’m interested in yet, would like the entire thing to play around with relationships if possible.

Do you think it could be made available via the API?

Even if history is hard to do, would appreciate current and going forward, or even just current data and I can start a time series on my side.

Thanks,

Rafael

From: Saber Khalfallah <saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io> > 
Sent: Friday, January 17, 2025 8:20 AM
To: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> >; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: [EXTERNAL] RE: historical CNF

Dear Rafael,

I hope this email finds you well.

Unfortunately, the specific data you're looking for isn't directly available via our API.

This is because it results from calculations involving multiple datasets related to freights and currency conversion.

However, if you can let us know the years and destinations you’re interested in, we’d be happy to create an Excel file containing the relevant historical data for you.

Please feel free to share the specifics, and we’ll get started on compiling the information.

Looking forward to your reply.

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah Customer Support

saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io>

To: Support Dnext <support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> >
Subject: historical CNF

Hi,

Are historical values for this matrix available via the API?

Best,

Rafael

emails.body_text:
Hi, 

 

Another question: I’m not seeing all the origins I see in the platform. Missing Brazil, USG among others. 

 

Thanks, 

Rafael

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Monday, January 27, 2025 2:44 PM
To: 'support@dnext.io' <support@dnext.io>
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

In addition to the question below, I have another one. 

 

How to interpret different FOB values for the same date/origin/delivery month combination?

 



 

Which to take?

 

Thanks, 
Rafael

 

From: Bucciarelli, Rafael 
Sent: Monday, January 27, 2025 1:40 PM
To: support@dnext.io <mailto:support@dnext.io> 
Subject: RE: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

Hi, 

 

Is this data being updated? Latest date I see available thru the API is 2025-01-21 but on the platform I see as late as 1/24. 

 

In addition could soybeans be added to this?

 

Thanks, 

Rafael

 

From: Saber Khalfallah <jira@dnext.atlassian.net <mailto:jira@dnext.atlassian.net> > 
Sent: Wednesday, January 22, 2025 9:04 AM
To: Bucciarelli, Rafael <Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com <mailto:Rafael.Bucciarelli@mlp.com> >
Subject: [EXTERNAL] DCS-845 historical CNF

 

—-—-—-— 

Reply above this line. 

Saber Khalfallah commented:

Hello Rafael,

Here is the code for the dataset containing data for Corn CNF to all destinations, FOB, as well as Freights:

Code: “zimb-a410fb85-d8ab-11ef-82fc-06cd53a4d901”

You will also receive automated emails notifying you each time the dataset is updated.

This will allow you to either download the file or refresh the API request.

If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out

Best regards,

Saber Khalfallah Customer Support

saber.khalfallah@dnext.io <mailto:saber.khalfallah@dnext.io>

Thanks,

Rafael

Many thanks!!

Best,

Rafael
